      <scene sNumber="3200" sType="scocontent" continueBtnType="DONE">
        <sceneitems>
          <ui uid="0" type="sceneHeader">
            <header id="h1">
              <![CDATA[What Are Customers Thinking?]]>
</header>
          </ui>
        </sceneitems>
        <slides>
          <slide sNumber="3205" type="BulletImageBuild" animType="animsync" endType="Continue">
            <ui uid="3" type="bodyBullet" width="500" x="left" y="top" margin="10" time="1" trans="slideRight" ease="QuintEaseOut" syncType="buildy" yPad="10">
              <bodyBullet id="bb1" order="2" time=".2" yPad="0">
                <![CDATA[How do you know when you are doing things right? Ask them! ]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb2" order="6">
                <![CDATA[Customer feedback is your most important tool for building on your strengths and eliminating weaknesses. Which of the following methods you use depends on your market and dealership.]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb3" order="10" fontSize="14">
                <![CDATA[<li><b>Ask customers yourself.</b> Ask customers how you can improve the service experience. Encourage feedback during the service visit, or during phone, email or text follow up</li>]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb4" order="12" fontSize="14">
                <![CDATA[<li><b>Use SSI and CSI.</b> Your market may be among those that use the J.D. Power customer survey results. While they are useful for helping you find and fix problems to increase satisfaction, remember that satisfaction is not the same as loyalty</li>]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb5" order="14" fontSize="14">
                <![CDATA[<li><b>Use the Customer Promoter Score.</b> Chrysler Group dealerships in North America and some other markets now use CPS as their primary feedback mechanism. Its focus on loyalty helps concentrate efforts on improving what you already do well</li>]]>
</bodyBullet>
            </ui>
            <ui uid="1" type="bodyImage" width="200" height="130" x="right" y="top" margin="10" trans="slideLeft" ease="BackEaseOut" time="1" syncType="buildy" yPad="25">
              <bodyImage id="i1" order="4" url="3205_1.jpg" yPad="0">
                <![CDATA[image 1]]>
</bodyImage>
              <bodyImage id="i2" order="8" url="3205_2.jpg">
                <![CDATA[Image 2]]>
</bodyImage>
              <bodyImage id="i3" order="12" url="3205_3.jpg">
                <![CDATA[Image 3]]>
</bodyImage>
            </ui>
          </slide>
          <slide sNumber="3210" type="BulletReplace" animType="timesync" endType="Continue">
            <ui uid="3" type="bodyBullet" width="700" x="left" y="top" margin="10" fontSize="18" time="1" trans="slideRight" ease="QuintEaseOut" yPad="0">
              <item id="bb0" order="1" timeIn=".5" timeOut="999">
                <![CDATA[Regardless of how you gather customer feedback, an effective process for using it to build loyalty should include the following:]]>
</item>
            </ui>
            <ui uid="6" type="bodyBullet"  x="left" y="60" width="640" margin="10" time="1" trans="slideRight" ease="QuintEaseOut" syncType="buildy" yPad="10">
              <item id="bb1" order="4" timeIn="2" timeOut="35" yPad="0">
             <![CDATA[<li>Get to the information behind the scores or initial answers. Keep asking “Why?” to discover the real reasons why a customer would or would not recommend you to friends and family, or doesn’t like a particular part of the experience</li>]]>
</item>
              <item id="bb2" order="6" timeIn="4" timeOut="35">
       <![CDATA[<li>Take immediate action. When talking to loyal customers to find out what specific things you do that keep them coming back, thank them for their input and explain what you are going to do to make sure all customers receive the same treatment</li>]]>
</item>
              <item id="bb3" order="8" timeIn="6" timeOut="35">
     <![CDATA[<li>If it’s a problem that you uncover, do what you can to fix it, right away.  If the situation can’t be immediately fixed, then apologize, and let them know what steps you’ll take to ensure it doesn’t happen again</li>]]>
</item>
            </ui>
            <ui uid="8" type="bodyBullet"  x="left" y="60" width="640" margin="10" time="1" trans="slideRight" ease="QuintEaseOut" syncType="buildy" yPad="10">
              <item id="bb4" order="10" timeIn="35.5" timeOut="999" yPad="0">
        <![CDATA[<li>Establish accountability. Managers should review trends and progress at weekly team meetings</li>]]>
</item>
              <item id="bb5" order="12" timeIn="36.5" timeOut="999">
   <![CDATA[<li>Make building customer loyalty a priority for everyone in the dealership</li>]]>
</item>
              <item id="bb6" order="14" timeIn="37.5" timeOut="999">
        <![CDATA[<li>Improve processes. Create teams to address strengths and weaknesses with process improvements</li>]]>
</item>
            </ui>
          </slide>
          <slide sNumber="3215" type="TextImageReplace" animType="timesync" endType="continue">
            <ui uid="2" type="BodyText" width="680" height="180" x="center" y="270" margin="0" fontAlign="center" effect="none" time="1" trans="slideLeft" ease="QuintEaseOut" syncType="replace">
              <bodyBullet id="bb1" timeIn=".5" timeOut="999">
                <![CDATA[Using customer feedback to guide dealership improvements is important, but it’s sort of like trying to steer a car by looking out the rear view mirror – you can only see where you’ve been, not where you want to go. </br>You can do a number of things starting today that help eliminate problems and build loyalty, without waiting for customer feedback.]]>
</bodyBullet>
